-- Nippon Steel Expands Osaka Plant Capacity to Meet Demand, Nikkei Reports
-- B y   Y u s u k e   M i y a z a w a
-- 2010-10-03T02:20:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-03/nippon-steel-expands-osaka-plant-capacity-to-meet-demand-nikkei-reports.html
Nippon Steel Corp. boosted the
capacity of a steel plant in Osaka prefecture, western Japan, to
make construction materials to meet rising demand in Asia,
the Nikkei newspaper reported, citing unidentified people at the
company.  The plant has been expanded at a cost of “a few billion
yen” to produce 592 types of H-beams used in construction,
double the number of varieties it previously made, according to
the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yusuke Miyazawa in Tokyo at 
